# Layered Architecture (Frontend)
/src
  /app          → Pages, routing, layout shells (thin)
  /features     → Feature modules with own components, hooks, API calls
  /components   → Shared UI primitives (Button, Input, Modal)
  /hooks        → Reusable custom hooks
  /lib          → Utilities, helpers, formatters
  /types        → Shared TypeScript types
  /services     → API clients, external integrations

# Rules Per Layer
- App layer: NO business logic, just composition
- Features: Self-contained, can be copied/deleted as a unit
- Components: Pure presentational, props-driven, no side effects
- Hooks: Single responsibility, composable
- Services: All API calls centralized, with error handling

# Data Flow
- Use React Query/SWR for server state
- Use Zustand/Jotai for client state only when necessary
- NEVER put fetch logic inside components — use hooks or services
- Form state: React Hook Form + Zod validation

# API Design
- RESTful naming: /resources/:id/actions
- Return typed responses using Zod schemas
- Centralized error handling with retry logic
- Loading and error states are FIRST-CLASS UI concerns

# Module Boundaries
- Features can import from components, hooks, lib, types
- Features CANNOT import from other features (prevents spaghetti)
- Shared code goes to /components, /hooks, or /lib
